 :tx/rationale "Create task: LIVESTORE-1: LiveStore type definition — the core abstraction that unifies DiskLayout and Store. CONTEXT: DiskLayout and Store are currently separate objects. 120+ call sites follow the pattern load_store() -> compute -> write_tx() -> exit. Every write invalidates the cache, forcing 2.5s rebuild. LiveStore eliminates this by owning both. APPROACH: (1) Define pub struct LiveStore { layout: DiskLayout, store: Store } in a new file crates/braid/src/live_store.rs. (2) LiveStore::open(path: &Path) -> Result<Self>: opens DiskLayout, calls load_store(), returns unified object. (3) LiveStore::store(&self) -> &Store: immutable access to the in-memory store for reads. (4) LiveStore::layout(&self) -> &DiskLayout: access to layout for list_tx_hashes and other filesystem ops. (5) LiveStore::path(&self) -> &Path: convenience accessor for the .braid directory path. (6) LiveStore must NOT impl Clone (it owns the mutable persistence handle). (7) LiveStore must impl Drop to ensure any pending state is flushed (store.bin write on drop if dirty). ACCEPTANCE: (A) LiveStore compiles with all fields. (B) LiveStore::open() returns a valid store identical to DiskLayout::open + load_store. (C) LiveStore::store() returns &Store with correct datom count. (D) No public constructor other than open(). DEPENDS-ON: none. FILE: crates/braid/src/live_store.rs (new file)"
